# Auto Commit & Push

After completing any code changes in this project:

1. Run `git add -A` to stage all relevant changes.
2. Create a concise commit message describing the **why** (1-2 sentences).
3. Commit immediately — do not wait for the user to ask.
4. Push to the current branch on `origin` (`git push origin HEAD`).
5. Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, tokens).

Skip auto-commit only when the user explicitly says not to commit, or when there are no file changes.
